The paper deals with learning-based approaches for multi-view stereopsis, which involves predicting depth maps from multiple images of a scene. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) category. The paper also proposes a novel loss formulation for handling occlusions and lighting changes, which involves enforcing consistency constraints. This is a machine learning (cs.LG) technique. The paper also deals with 3D reconstruction, which falls under the graphics (cs.GR) category. The paper proposes a method for unsupervised learning, which involves adapting existing CNNs to datasets without ground-truth 3D by unsupervised finetuning. This is an artificial intelligence (cs.AI) technique. Lastly, the paper deals with robotics (cs.RO) as the proposed method can be used for 3D reconstruction in robotics applications.
